# Union-merge append-only data files so Phase 2 matrix legs don't lose each
# other's rows during concurrent `git pull --rebase` retries.
#
# Without this, Git's default recursive merge with `-X ours` silently drops
# the second-pushing leg's rows: Git's patch-similarity heuristic sees both
# legs appending lines at the same file offset and marks the later patch as
# "already upstream" — erasing real data. Union merge concatenates both
# sides' hunks, which is exactly what we want for append-only logs/CSVs.
#
# Do NOT add JSON files here — union merge produces invalid JSON by
# concatenating conflicting objects. Single-writer discipline (Phase 1 only,
# self-hosted runner serializes) is how JSON files stay consistent.
box-office-tracker/data/seat-counts.csv         merge=union
box-office-tracker/data/polymarket-markets.csv  merge=union
box-office-tracker/data/run-log.md              merge=union
